# BuildKit per-Dockerfile ignore (overrides the repo root .dockerignore for this build).
# Whitelist: only what the Godot avatar example needs. Bundles every avatar (VRM + Live2D
# models) and the subset of ThirdParty/gd_cubism the Dockerfile's gdcubism stage needs to
# compile the Linux Live2D extension (source + godot-cpp + the license-gated Cubism SDK,
# which must already be on disk - it cannot be fetched during the build).
*
!Directory.Build.props
!Directory.Build.targets
!src/Directory.*
!src/SIPSorceryMedia.Abstractions/**
!src/SIPSorceryMedia.FFmpeg/**
!src/SIPSorcery/**
!src/SIPSorcery.VP8/**
!examples/WebRTCExamples/AvatarPipeline/**
!examples/WebRTCExamples/WebRTCGodotAvatar/**
**/bin/**
**/obj/**
**/.godot/**
examples/WebRTCExamples/WebRTCGodotAvatar/ThirdParty/**
!examples/WebRTCExamples/WebRTCGodotAvatar/ThirdParty/gd_cubism/SConstruct
!examples/WebRTCExamples/WebRTCGodotAvatar/ThirdParty/gd_cubism/SConspage
!examples/WebRTCExamples/WebRTCGodotAvatar/ThirdParty/gd_cubism/bi.scons
!examples/WebRTCExamples/WebRTCGodotAvatar/ThirdParty/gd_cubism/src/**
!examples/WebRTCExamples/WebRTCGodotAvatar/ThirdParty/gd_cubism/doc_classes/**
!examples/WebRTCExamples/WebRTCGodotAvatar/ThirdParty/gd_cubism/godot-cpp/**
!examples/WebRTCExamples/WebRTCGodotAvatar/ThirdParty/gd_cubism/demo/addons/**
!examples/WebRTCExamples/WebRTCGodotAvatar/ThirdParty/gd_cubism/thirdparty/CubismSdkForNative-5-r.5/Core/**
!examples/WebRTCExamples/WebRTCGodotAvatar/ThirdParty/gd_cubism/thirdparty/CubismSdkForNative-5-r.5/Framework/**
# The gd_cubism addon bin/ carries only Windows dlls on disk; the image gets its Linux .so
# from the gdcubism build stage instead (and the .gdextension + C# wrappers come from the
# addon folder as normal). Keep the Windows binaries out of the context.
examples/WebRTCExamples/WebRTCGodotAvatar/addons/gd_cubism/bin/**
**/.git/**
